replies.bodyText:
While re-reviewing this earlier today, I noticed that the way we handle n-tier here, is that we set all provided products of the hierarchy to the top marketing object.
So if ProductA has ProvidedProductB, and ProvidedProductB itself has ProvidedProductC, then we end up with this DTO structure:
ProductA {
    providedProducts: [ ProvidedProductB, ProvidedProductC ]
} 

Shouldn't it instead be like this?:
ProductA {
    providedProducts: [ 
        ProvidedProductB { 
            providedProducts: [ ProvidedProductC ]
        }
    ]
}

Again, sorry if this was already discussed in more detail and I missed it!

